---

<BaseLayout title="About" description="A bit about Debangan Thakuria — backend engineer, reader, writer.">
  <article>
    <div class="mb-8">
      <span class="text-2xl" style="font-family: var(--font-family-mono); color: var(--color-purple);" aria-hidden="true">(=^･ω･^=)</span>
    </div>

    <h1 class="text-4xl mb-8" style="font-family: var(--font-family-heading); font-weight: 600; color: var(--color-text);">
      about <span class="gradient-text">me</span>
    </h1>

    <div class="prose mb-14">
      <p>
        I'm Debangan Thakuria — a backend software engineer with about four and a half years of
        experience, mostly in distributed systems and API design. I like building things that are
        simple, correct, and boring in the best possible way.
      </p>
      <p>
        I'm also a reader. I grew up on Hardy Boys, Nancy Drew, Famous Five, Agatha Christie,
        Goosebumps — the usual suspects. Somewhere along the way that expanded into manga and light
        novels, then web novels and the occasional fantasy or sci-fi epic. The stories I gravitate
        towards tend to feature capable protagonists who try to do the right thing, even when it's
        hard. You might know the term <em>competency porn</em> — that's exactly it. Characters who
        are genuinely good at what they do, and watching them grow and navigate the world is the
        whole point.
      </p>
      <p>
        I've recently started writing my own web novel. Slowly, which is fine — it's as much about
        learning to write and tell stories as it is about finishing anything.
      </p>
      <p>
        Outside of all that: I go to the gym, keep up with global news, watch anime and the
        occasional fantasy show or film. I tend to prefer warm spaces, cosy evenings, and very
        good tea.
      </p>
      <p>
        This site is a place to put down things I'd otherwise lose to scattered notes. No theme, no
        niche — just whatever's on my mind.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Grouped socials -->
    <div class="flex flex-col gap-10">
      {groups.map(group => (
        <div>
          <h2 class="text-xs font-semibold uppercase tracking-widest mb-4" style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">
            {group.label}
          </h2>
          <div class="flex flex-col gap-2">
            {group.links.map(s => (
              <a
                href={s.href}
                target="_blank"
                rel="noopener noreferrer"
                class="social-link"
                style={`--brand: ${s.color}; --brand-dark: ${s.darkColor};`}
              >
                <span class="social-icon" set:html={s.icon} />
                <div class="flex items-baseline gap-2">
                  <span class="text-sm font-semibold" style="color: var(--color-text);">{s.label}</span>
                  <span class="text-xs" style="color: var(--color-text-muted);">{s.handle}</span>
                </div>
                <span class="social-arrow" aria-hidden="true">↗</span>
              </a>
            ))}
          </div>
        </div>
      ))}
    </div>
  </article>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .social-link {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    gap: 0.875rem;
    padding: 0.75rem 1rem;
    border-radius: 0.75rem;
    background: var(--color-surface);
    text-decoration: none;
    transition: transform 0.15s ease;
    position: relative;
  }

  .social-link:hover {
    transform: translateX(4px);
  }

  .social-icon {
    display: flex;
    align-items: center;
    justify-content: center;
    width: 2rem;
    height: 2rem;
    border-radius: 0.5rem;
    background: var(--brand);
    color: #fff;
    flex-shrink: 0;
    opacity: 0.9;
    transition: opacity 0.15s ease;
  }

  .social-link:hover .social-icon { opacity: 1; }

  .social-arrow {
    margin-left: auto;
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-muted);
    opacity: 0;
    transform: translateX(-4px);
    transition: opacity 0.15s ease, transform 0.15s ease;
  }

  .social-link:hover .social-arrow {
    opacity: 1;
    transform: translateX(0);
  }

  :global(html.dark) .social-icon {
    background: transparent;
    color: var(--brand-dark);
    border: 1px solid var(--brand-dark);
  }
</style>
